================================================================================
Relationship to the dual-chip repos
================================================================================

This is a single-chip variant that runs the gateway (net core) and the
Zigbee/Lua engine (main core) on one ESP32-S3, calling directly across a
compile-time bridge (`components/mono_bridge/`) instead of the SPI/HAP link.
It reuses the shared ZHAC components rather than vendoring copies:

- zhac-components — mixed Apache-2.0 / AGPL-3.0-or-later (same project, separate repo)
- embedded-zhc    — Apache-2.0 (same project, separate repo)
- zhac-main-core  — AGPL-3.0-or-later (same project; its `lua_cjson` MIT sources
                    are reused here through a CMake override in
                    `components/lua_cjson/`, not vendored a second time)
- zhac-net-core   — AGPL-3.0-or-later (the gateway layer in `main/` derives from it)
- www-spa         — AGPL-3.0-or-later (built into `dist/` and embedded)

These are resolved from sibling checkouts at build time (see README).

